            "fact_text": "<p>Environmental Impact & SustainabilityThere are significant differences between mined diamonds and lab grown diamonds. Local communities and wildlife are often externally displaced due to the vast amounts of land required for traditional diamond mining activities. In terms of water use, the extraction of diamonds through traditional means also leads to soil erosion. The operation of heavy machinery to extract diamonds through traditional methods leads to a large carbon footprint from fuel used, and contributes to deforestation, decline of biodiversity, and long-term negative consequences for both the environment and ecosystems.Lab grown diamonds are created in laboratory environments that use fewer resources than traditional mined diamonds and therefore have less negative environmental impact. Lab grown diamonds do not involve land destruction or habitat loss in their creation. Lab grown diamonds have also developed fully traceable records of the process, date of creation, and all methods used. With a growing trend worldwide to purchase goods and services in an environmentally conscious and ethically responsible manner, lab grown diamonds are not only environmentally friendly products; but they are nearly indistinguishable from the beauty, strength, and optical properties of natural mined diamonds.</p>"
